               <msContents>
                  <summary>Maṣḥafa qǝddāse “Missal” (fols. 9vb-109ra):
 I) Anaphoras
 I-1)
                     Anaphora of St Epiphanius of Cyprus (fol. 9vb)
 I-2) Second Anaphora of St
                     Gregory (“Christmas-liturgy of St Gregory”) (fol. 14va)
 I-3) Anaphora of
                     St Cyril of Alexandria (fol. 19va)
 I-4) Anaphora of St Dioscorus of
                     Alexandria (fol. 23vb)
 I-5) Anaphora of St Gregory (“Hosanna-liturgy of St
                     Gregory”) (fol. 25va)
 I-6) Anaphora of St Athanasius of Alexandria (fol.
                     31rb)
 I-7) Anaphora of St Basil of Caesarea (fol. 44rb)
 I-8) Anaphora
                     of St John Chrysostom (fol. 54va)
 I-9) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug (fol.
                     58vb)
 I-10) Anaphora of St John, son of Thunder (fol. 60vb)
 I-11)
                     Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox Fathers of Nicaea (fol. 68ra)
 I-12) Anaphora
                     of Our Lord Jesus Christ (fol. 69ra)
 I-13) Anaphora of Our Lady by St
                     Cyriacus of Behnesa (fol. 72ra)
 I-14) Anaphora of the Apostles (fol.
                     82ra)
 II) Ṣalota ʿǝṭān “Prayer of the Incense” (fol. 16vb)
 III)
                     Śǝrʿāta qǝddāse “Ordinary of the Mass” (fol. 103va)
 IV) Daily Office
                     Prayers and Litanies (fols. 109ra)
 
 Additio 1.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                        <locus target="#8ra">8ra</locus>: ስብሐት፡ ለእግዚአብሔር፡  ዘአፈጸመኒ፡ ሊተ፡ ለኃጥእ፡  ገብሩ፨ 
                        ገብረ፡  አድኀኒ፡ <locus target="#8ra">8ra</locus>: Praise be to God who has enabled
                        me to complete (the writing), me, His sinful servant. Gabra ʾAdḫani. The name
                        Gabra ʾAdḫani was added in red, in a secondary hand, the same which added the
                        second part of the name, ʾAdḫani, to the supplication formulas. </colophon>
                  </msItem>
                  
