                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the king; (part of the) name
                           of the donor; first words (headings or parts of headings) of constituent
                           texts; directives for the ministers; some of the musical notation signs
                           above the lines; most of the abbreviations; elements of the punctuation
                           signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.
 The text on page 109r as well
                           as the incipit parts of some texts (e. g., fols. 60vb, 69va) are written
                           alternately in red and black lines.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">It cannot be excluded that more than
                        one scribe took part in writing: cp. <locus from="18v" to="19r">18v-19r</locus>,
                        28v-29r.</handNote>
